The paper deals with channel estimation and beamforming in massive MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel technique for analog channel estimation, which involves designing a receiver architecture and analyzing its performance, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses transmit beamforming, which is a key aspect of massive MIMO systems and is studied in the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
